  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Colombia: Technical Assistance to Individual Productive Projects - Phase II</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The objective of the project is to contribute to the economic reincorporation process of former Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia&#x2014;People&apos;s Army (FARC-EP in Spanish) members in Colombia, through assistance and/or comprehensive technical support to their individual productive projects. This promotes an adequate investment of the economic support granted by the National Government, in accordance with the guidelines and criteria established by Agency for Reincorporation and Normalization. The primary purpose of the technical assistance to the individual productive projects is to enhance the quality of the design, implementation, development and/or growth and impact of the venture by strengthening specific individual or organizational capacities and reducing risks throughout the full lifecycle of the productive reincorporation project. Therefore, the Comprehensive Technical Assistance Plan implemented with the beneficiary projects encompasses technical-productive aspects, marketing-sales, empowerment and organizational strengthening, education for financial management and environmental management.</narrative>
  </description>
